::MY OWN HEALING::
When I work with Women and their health, we dive deep into the deep held stories and beliefs residing within and are manifesting in the physical body as well as in their life.
.
I do this with myself as well. The pattern I am working with and through at this moment in my life is the blueprint of ABORTION.
.
This pattern residing within my reproductive system- which stems from actual, physical experiences- has led me to begin a multitude of creative endeavors and paths...Yet never seeing them through to completion and starting new paths. .

Some of these include:
▪My dream and life as a singer/performer. Musicals and choirs were my passion- and I was really good- until I suddenly stopped it when I went to college in fear of not being good enough.
▪My dream and life as a professional artist- yet as soon as I began showing in galleries and selling high ticket pieces, I ended it abruptly and went back to school...leaving behind several unfinished pieces that are waiting to be completed.
▪My life and dream as a Nature and Forest Therapy Guide- yet as soon as I was 1 step away from certification, I decided to focus on Women's health instead.
.
And there are others.
What this pattern has created is a consistent feeling of "I will never achieve my dreams" and which is debilitating.
.
So I am now healing and transforming this blueprint by fully birthing all those creative aspirations I gestated all those years ago.
. 
I am taking voice lessons. 
I purchased art supplies to finish the uncompleted pieces. 
I am setting up meetings to finish my certification.
.
Healing is not just physical. It manifests as physical, but is usually always rooted in the emotional and spiritual.
.
What generative blueprints and patterns do you see in your life? What step can you take to transform them, to heal them? What new creative and generative pattern do you want to create?
.
.

The "Cool Walk" and "Cool Skip" is one one of the 6 ESSENTIAL dribbles needed for effective guard play. "Ball turning," not carrying, is one of the 14 #Ball #Control Principles needed to develop into a #monster handler! The Cool Walk/Skip is THE most important dribble concept that can be taught.

The "Cool Walk/Skip" allows for you to:

1. Control Pace and defender (won't be sped up) without body contact unless #neccessary
2. Handle Pressure/Protect the Ball
3. Transition seamlessly into protection breakdowns or faceup atttacks
4. Patiently wait for plays
*5. Conserve energy
6. Flow 
7. Offset defensive quickness and size in most instances

Do you come from a place of love for yourself? Think about the things you do out of love for others. When you care deeply for someone, you will climb mountains for them. You will help them with their problems, lift them up when they're down, support them when they succeed, etc. Love motivates you to do and be your best for someone. If you can give that much to someone else, why can't you work on giving it to yourself? If you have the same love to yourself that you give to others; if you worked just as hard, imagine how far you could lift yourself up? Think about how much more care and support you'd give yourself if you thought about loving yourself the same way you love others. #headhighheartforward
